 formative of the identities and agencies that seemingly bear on it as causes. Focusing on the particular sites where violence is inflicted and where its subjects and objects are articulated, the book traces the intersection of violence and architecture from socialist modernization, through ethnic and nationalist conflict, to postwar reconstruction.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aArchitecture and societyzKosovo (Republic). 0aArchitecture and warzKosovo (Republic). 0aBuildingsxWar damagezKosovo (Republic). 0aKosovo War, 1998-1999xDestruction and pillage. 7aARCHITECTURE / Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477622640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804776226423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804776226.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles